Words.Name: Wicked
Words.Definition: Having committed unrighteous acts (kotu, kotuluk/ahlahsizlik pesinde olan)
Words.Example: Now here she was forced to make her living among all the black scum of this wicked city.

Words.Name: Nefarious
Words.Definition: Extremely wicked (cok kotu, alcakca)

Words.Name: Contingency
Words.Definition: A possible event or occurrence or result
Words.Example: When you insure anything, you are contracting to receive some specified payoff in the event of a clearly defined contingency.

Words.Name: Excerpt
Words.Definition: A short extract from a film, broadcast, or piece of music or writing
Words.Example: Number the main ideas in the order they are developed in the excerpt given.

Words.Name: Trait
Words.Definition: A distinguishing feature of the objects personal nature
Words.Example: In the past, rubies were associated with many positive traits.

Words.Name: Legitimacy
Words.Definition: The state or quality of being legitimate or in comformity with law (mesruluk)
Words.Example: A year after his father died, kim jong eun solidified his legitimacy and his hold on power with the successful launch of a three-stage rocket that put a satellite into orbit.

Words.Name: Portrayal
Words.Definition: The act of process of portraying using words, acting or painting; description (betimleme, tasvir; tanimlama)
Words.Example: Perhaps best remembered was his surprise portrayal of betsy ross.

Words.Name: To reconcile
Words.Definition: To make different things come together or resolve a matter (uzlastirmak)
Words.Example: See if you can reconcile the following hypothetical statements, both of which could be true.

Words.Name: Intermediary
Words.Definition: A negotiator who acts as a link between parties
Words.Example: His central role as priest—intermediary between congregation and god—is diminished.

Words.Name: Perjury
Words.Definition: Act of deliberately lying under oath (yalanci sahitlik)
Words.Example: I would not get you convicted of perjury.

Words.Name: Freight
Words.Definition: Sending of goods or the goods themselves (nakliye veya nakliyede tasinan mallar)
Words.Example: They were going to jump on the night freight train and ride out of town.

Words.Name: To incur
Words.Definition: To encounter something inconvenient or harmful, to become liable or subject to (kotu bir seye maruz kalmak, cekmek zorunda kalmak)
Words.Example: It appeared that he had only stung the leg, not incurred a deeper injury.

Words.Name: Attic
Words.Definition: A space or room just below the roof of a building
Words.Example: There are five attic bedrooms.

Words.Name: Upheaval
Words.Definition: A great change, causing or involving difficulty or trouble (ani ve büyük degisiklik)
Words.Example: The long garbage strike in 1970 caused much political upheaval.

Words.Name: To pertain to
Words.Definition: Be related to (bir seyle ilgili/alakali/baglantili olmak)
Words.Example: We are only interested in the parts of the proposals that pertain to local issues.

Words.Name: To strike a balance
Words.Definition: Accept parts of both things in order to satisfy some of the demands of both sides in an argument, rather than all the demands of just one side (ortada bulusmak)
Words.Example: We need to strike a balance between accuracy and practicality.

Words.Name: To keep
Words.Definition: To have or retain possession of
Words.Example: My father would keep the best for himself.

Words.Name: Inference
Words.Definition: A guess that you make or an opinion that you form based on the information that you have (cikarim)
Words.Example: We contextualize, filter, draw conclusions, and make inferences, in part, based on someone’s physical attributes.

Words.Name: To aspires to
Words.Definition: To have a strong desire to do or become something
Words.Example: The actor has not been in a movie for then years, but he still aspires to stardom.

Words.Name: Firmly
Words.Definition: Strongly, forcefully, certainly
Words.Example:
We are firmly committed to reducing unemployment.

he shook my hand firmly and climbed into the taxi.

Words.Name: Versatile
Words.Definition: Able to adapt or be adapted to many different functions or activities
Words.Example: He was versatile enough to play either position.

Words.Name: To procure
Words.Definition: Get by special effort (temin etmek)
Words.Example: This very morning, she announces, she has managed to procure what might be the last two crates of peaches in france.

Words.Name: Resolve
Words.Definition: A strong determination to do something
Words.Example: Superheroes succeed because they have the resolve to keep fighting even when a situation seems hopeless.
